@gnossienne: That really should make sense... *except*, your model requires that there are now individual genetically smart Africans and genetically dumb Africans.  Which means that when they get together and marry, (or have grandchildren in a backcross to be technical) you should see huge variations in IQ depending on which alleles get passed on.  But ... none come up in GWAS studies.

